    {
      "topic": "Miscellaneous",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "Tip: Different profile / user in Chrome without extensions"
        },
        {
          "title": "Use the proper <code>lang</code>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Use a CDN"
        },
        {
          "title": "Try to avoid redirects, these can impose high latency overhead"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Audits",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "The optimisation of the visual progress is terrible\n    The website does not show any content till every content is loaded\n    This problem leads up to a huge visual progress area"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "HTTP optimisation",
      "items": [
        {
          "topic": "HTTP/1",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Don’t <a href=\"http://i.imgur.com/HkoOZYp.jpg\">include many (small) files</a>:\n    HTTP/1 can only deal with 6-8 files at a time"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "HTTP/2",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "<a href=\"https://tools.keycdn.com/http2-test\">Enable HTTP2</a>\n<a href=\"https://http2.github.io/\">HTTP/2</a> is an new protocol that is introduced to increase\n    the performance, specifically, end-user perceived latency, network and server resource\n    usage. One major advantage is to allow the use of a single connection from browsers to\n    a Web site."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Caching",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "Make sure that all non-HTML files have a caching parameter specified <a href=\"https://varvy.com/pagespeed/cache-control.html\">more info</a>"
        },
        {
          "title": "Specify an expiration at least one week in the future for resources"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Minification",
      "items": [
        {
          "topic": "Images",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Compress images (such as with <a href=\"https://i.onthe.io/google_speed\">PageSpeed Image Optimizer</a>\n    or the techniques <a href=\"https://developers.google.com/speed/docs/insights/OptimizeImages\">described by Google</a>)"
            },
            {
              "title": "Images with little detail and small colour pallet, are smaller with png format instead of jpg. If possible, use svg."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "CSS",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Minify CSS"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "HTML",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Minify HTML"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "JavaScript",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Minify the JavaScript: either manually through\n    <a href=\"https://jscompress.com/\"><code>jscompress</code></a>,\n    <a href=\"https://www.minifier.org/\"><code>minifier.org</code></a>, or\n    with something UglifyJS, potentially through Gulp"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Fonts",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Add a fallback font"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use font subsetting"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Perceived Performance",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "Use a placeholder for background images (blurred/loading like) to\n    indicate that here is and should be an image at that position"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Performance",
      "items": [
        {
          "topic": "Images",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Use newer image types (<code>.webp</code>; <code>.jxr</code> <a href=\"https://i.onthe.io/jxr\">jpg -&gt; jxr</a>)"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use inline images for the hero image instead of a background image"
            },
            {
              "title": "Add <code>srcset</code>s and <code>sizes</code>"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/picture\"><code>&lt;picture&gt;</code></a>s"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use (inline) <code>svg</code> when possible"
            },
            {
              "title": "Serve images in a proper size\n    This will improve load time and save cellular data\n    If you provide images larger than the user needs, you are just wasting bytes"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use client hints"
            },
            {
              "title": "SVG's are smaller but they do not render always faster than other formats. Especially when they are very complex. Render speed is also included with the load time of content."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "CSS",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Add inline critical CSS (see <a href=\"https://css-tricks.com/authoring-critical-fold-css/\">Authoring Critical Above-the-Fold CSS</a>)"
            },
            {
              "title": "Remove unused CSS files"
            },
            {
              "title": "<a href=\"http://i.imgur.com/lc1K2xM.jpg\">Remove unused selectors</a> (see <a href=\"https://unused-css.com\">unused-css</a>)"
            },
            {
              "title": "Reduce render-blocking stylesheets if it isn’t critical (such as with <a href=\"https://github.com/filamentgroup/loadCSS\"><code>loadCSS</code></a>)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "HTML",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Remove inline styles"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use a minimal amount of classes"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "JavaScript",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Concatenate JavaScript files"
            },
            {
              "title": "Load JavaScript and CSS later so they don’t block rendering"
            },
            {
              "title": "Move script links in <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> to bottom of document or add <code>defer</code> and <code>async</code> if they are\n    not necessary to render above-the-fold content"
            },
            {
              "title": "Remove jQuery"
            },
            {
              "title": "Add small, single purpose scripts inline"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Fonts",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Use something like <code>font-display: swap</code>"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic": "Animations",
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Remove <code>overflow: hidden;</code> from animating elements and their parent container as\n    <code>overflow: hidden</code> makes all children trigger Layout"
            },
            {
              "title": "Look out for <a href=\"https://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/speed/high-performance-animations/\">Paint and Layout triggering effects</a>"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use <code>transform</code>, <code>clip</code> and <code>opacity</code> for high performing animations <a href=\"https://csstriggers.com/\">CSS Triggers</a>"
            },
            {
              "title": "In JavaScript use <code>requestAnimationFrame</code> instead of <code>setInterval</code> for higher performance (<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/nl/docs/Web/API/Window/requestAnimationFrame\">MDN rAF</a>)"
            },
            {
              "title": "Use <code>will-change</code> wisely (<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/will-change\">MDN will-change</a>)"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "topic": "Backend optimisation",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "If you’re using templates (such as in wordpress), make sure they don’t\n    include things you aren’t using"
        }
      ]
    }
